content:
Report on Entitlements

Use custom report types to define report criteria that users can use to run and create reports on entitlements, service contracts, and contract line items.

Available in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud.

To create or update entitlement management custom report types: Manage Custom Report Types
To create and run reports based on entitlement management custom report types: Create and Customize Reports

After setup, Salesforce org includes:

- Accounts with entitlements with contacts
- Service contracts with contract line items
- Service contracts with entitlements
- Cases with milestones (this report type can't be customized)

From Setup, enter Report Types in the Quick Find box, then select Report Types.
Define a new custom report type. You can't select entitlements as a primary object.
Update a custom report type's name, description, and deployment status.
Delete a custom report type. 

If you delete a custom report type, all data stored is deleted.

See also: Set Up Entitlements, Set Up Service Contracts
title: Setting up Custom Reports for Entitlement Management
